Class TopicInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.cloud.pubsub.TopicInfo

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Topic

    public class TopicInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A Google Cloud Pub/Sub topic. A topic is a named resource to which messages are sent by publishers. Subscribers can receive messages sent to a topic by creating subscriptions.
    See Also:
    Pub/Sub Data Model, Serialized Form

      • name

        public java.lang.String name()
        Returns the name of the topic. The name must start with a letter, and contain only letters ([A-Za-z]), numbers ([0-9]), dashes (-), underscores (_), periods (.), tildes (~), plus (+) or percent signs (%). It must be between 3 and 255 characters in length and cannot begin with the string goog.
